ves'%20company%20in%20exchange%20for%20awarding%20them%20a%20government%20contract%2C%20said%20the%20DOJ%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fusao-dc%2Fmedia%2F1353911%2Fdl%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20the%20indictment%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20Kim%20and%20Messenger%20of%20New%20York%20first%20secured%20a%20government%20contract%20to%20provide%20training%20for%20pilots%20in%20the%20US%20Navy%20from%202018%20to%202019%2C%20that%20Burke%20had%20advocated%20for.%20The%20Navy%20ended%20the%20contract%20and%20ordered%20the%20two%20CEOs%20not%20to%20contact%20Burke.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20indictment%20alleges%20that%20Kim%20and%20Messenger%20reached%20out%20multiple%20times%20to%20Burke%2C%20eventually%20having%20a%20call%20in%20which%20Burke%20said%20he%20wanted%20to%20work%20with%20the%20company%2C%20which%20Kim%20said%20would%20need%20to%20be%20attached%20to%20a%20deal%2C%20per%20the%20indictment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DOJ%20indictment%20alleges%20that%20Burke%20met%20with%20Kim%20and%20Messenger%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20in%20July%202021%20where%20he%20agreed%20to%20influence%20other%20officers%20to%20award%20another%20contract%20to%20Kim%20and%20Messenger's%20company%2C%20a%20contract%20that%20Kim%20valued%20in%20the%20%26quot%3Btriple%20digit%20millions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20alleged%2C%20Burke%20later%20ordered%20his%20staff%20to%20award%20Messenger%20and%20Kim's%20company%20a%20contract%20to%20train%20naval%20personnel%20in%20Italy%20and%20Spain.%20According%20to%20the%20release%2C%20the%20contract%20was%20worth%20%24355%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBurke%20began%20working%20at%20the%20company%20in%20October%202022%20at%20a%20starting%20salary%20of%20%24500%2C000%20and%20a%20grant%20of%20100%2C000%20stock%20options%2C%20said%20the%20DOJ%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAdmiral%20Burke%20used%20his%20public%20office%20and%20his%20four-star%20status%20for%20his%20private%20gain%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20US%20Attorney%20Matthew%20M.%20Graves%20in%20the%20DOJ%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20law%20does%20not%20make%20exceptions%20for%20admirals%20or%20CEOs.%C2%A0Those%20who%20pay%20and%20receive%20bribes%20must%20be%20held%20accountable.%C2%A0The%20urgency%20is%20at%20its%20greatest%20when%2C%20as%20here%2C%20senior%20government%20officials%20and%20senior%20executives%20are%20allegedly%20involved%20in%20the%20corruption%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Burke's%20lawyer%2C%20Timothy%20Parlatore%2C%20Burke%20made%20his%20first%20appearance%20in%20court%20in%20Florida%20late%20Friday%20afternoon%20and%20is%20set%20to%20be%20arraigned%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20intend%20to%20go%20to%20trial%20and%20we%20expect%20that%20he%20will%20be%20found%20not%20guilty%2C%26quot%3B%20Paralotre%20told%20the%20USNI%20News.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20biggest%20problem%20with%20this%20indictment%20is%20the%20timeline.%20The%20DOJ%20wrongly%20believes%20that%20there%20was%20a%20job%20offer%20and%20job%20agreement%20far%20earlier%20than%20there%20was.%20There%20is%20no%20quid%20pro%20quo%2C%20no%20job%20for%20contracts%20whatsoever%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20looks%20odd%20he%20did%20later%20go%20work%20for%20them%20but%20he%20did%20not%20get%20into%20serious%20contract%20negotiations%20until%20the%20appropriate%20time%20and%20with%20the%20appropriate%20permissions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20the%20US%20Navy%20told%20USNI%20News%20the%20service%20%26quot%3Bcooperated%20with%20this%20investigation%20from%20the%20onset.%20We%20take%20this%20matter%20very%20seriously%20and%20will%20continue%20to%20cooperate%20with%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretired-us-navy-4-star-admiral-arrested-alleged-bribery2024-6%5C%22%3EBusi